  "name": "Maneuver: Maneuvering Attack",
  "ownership": {
    "default": 0
  },
  "type": "feat",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>When you hit a creature with a weapon attack, you can expend one superiority die to maneuver one of your comrades into a more advantageous position. You add the superiority die to the attack's damage roll, and you choose a friendly creature who can see or hear you. That creature can use its reaction to move up to half its speed without provoking opportunity attacks from the target of your attack.</p>\n<p>Beginning at 7th fighter level, you can choose up to two friendly creatures who can see or hear you.</p>\n<p>Beginning at 15th fighter level, you can choose any number of friendly creatures who can see or hear you.</p>",
